(method, but also the exact place where students often go wrong. Learning improves when) Tj
T*
(the student compares correct reasoning with incorrect reasoning.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect diet and nutrient-function questions. The most effective habit is to) Tj
T*
(read the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a) Tj
T*
(similar question alone. This turns Nutrition into something the student can genuinely) Tj
T*
(study and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Nutrition should first be understood as a biological idea before it is treated as an) Tj
T*
(exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand balanced diet, nutrients, and food functions because it) Tj
T*
(controls how questions in Nutrition are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Nutrition uses the correct process explanation and explains why) Tj
T*
(that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Explaining why proteins and carbohydrates play different roles is the type of) Tj
T*
(application that helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Nutrition.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind balanced diet, nutrients, and) Tj
T*
(food functions.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct process explanation step by step instead of jumping to the answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on explaining why proteins and carbohydrates play) Tj
T*
(different roles.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in balanced diet, nutrients, and food functions that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Nutrition step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on diet and nutrient-function questions.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid calling every food nutrient an energy source while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
