(Lesson Vocabulary) Tj
T*
(- Nutrition: The main topic being studied, understood here as nutrition examines how) Tj
T*
(organisms obtain and use food for growth and health.) Tj
T*
(- Core Focus: The main idea the learner must understand in this lesson: balanced diet,) Tj
T*
(nutrients, and food functions.) Tj
T*
(- Application: The point where the explanation is used in practice, such as explaining) Tj
T*
(why proteins and carbohydrates play different roles.) Tj
T*
(- Common Error: A repeated learner difficulty in this topic, for example calling every) Tj
T*
(food nutrient an energy source.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Nutrition: balanced diet, nutrients, and food) Tj
T*
(functions.) Tj
T*
(- Calling every food nutrient an energy source.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Nutrition without checking whether the method matches the question being) Tj
T*
(asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
